tex":"Solve the simultaneous equations.\nYou must show all your working.\n\n\\[\\begin{cases}\n5x + 8y = 4 \\\\\n\\frac{1}{2}x + 3y = 7\n\\end{cases}\\]\n\ny =","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"solve"},{"id":"0580-2019MayJune-Paper22-Q15","paper":"2019MayJune-Paper22","qnum":15,"marks":3,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.13","d":2,"cat":"number","topic":"Percentages","qtype":"percentages","g":"mixed","src":"0580/22/M/J/19 Q15","year":2019,"session":"MayJune","tex":"Shona buys a chair in a sale for \\$435.60.\nThis is a reduction of 12\\% on the original price.\nCalculate the original price of the chair.\n\n\\$","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate"},{"id":"0580-2019MayJune-Paper22-Q16","paper":"2019MayJune-Paper22","qnum":16,"marks":3,"topics":["Number","Algebra and graphs"],"s":"2.6","d":2,"cat":"algebra","topic":"Inequalities","qtype":"inequalities","g":"inequality","src":"0580/22/M/J/19 Q16","year":2019,"session":"MayJune","tex":"(a) By shading the unwanted regions of the grid, find and label the region R that satisfies the three inequalities.\n\\[y \\leq -12x + 6,\\quad y \\leq 3x - 4,\\quad x + y \\leq 5\\]\n\n(b) Find the largest value of \\(x + y\\) in the region R, where x and y are integers.","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":2},{"label":"(b)","marks":1}],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"find"},{"id":"0580-2019MayJune-Paper22-Q17","paper":"2019MayJune-Paper22","qnum":17,"marks":3,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.4","d":2,"cat":"number","topic":"Fractions, decimals, percentages","qtype":"fractions, decimals, percentages","g":"mixed","src":"0580/22/M/J/19 Q17","year":2019,"session":"MayJune","tex":"Write as a single fraction in its simplest form.\n\\[\\dfrac{2x}{x+3} + \\dfrac{x+3}{x-5}\\]","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"recall","cmd":"write"},{"id":"0580-2019MayJune-Paper22-Q18","paper":"2019MayJune-Paper22","qnum":18,"marks":3,"topics":["Statistics"],"s":"9.7","d":2,"cat":"statistics","topic":"Histograms","qtype":"histograms","g":"mixed","src":"0580/22/M/J/19 Q18","year":2019,"session":"MayJune","tex":"The table shows the number of people in different age groups at a cinema.\n\\begin{tabular}{|l|l|}\n\\hline\nAge (years) & Number of people \\\\\n\\hline\n15 ≤ y < 25 & 35 \\\\\n25 ≤ y < 30 & 32 \\\\\n30 ≤ y < 50 & 44 \\\\\n50 ≤ y < 80 & 12 \\\\\n\\hline\n\\end{tabular}\n\nDexter draws a histogram to show this information.\nThe height of the bar he draws for the group 15 ≤ y < 25 is 7 cm.\nCalculate the height of each of the remaining bars.\n\n25 ≤ y < 30  \\\\\n30 ≤ y < 50  \\\\\n50 ≤ y < 80","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate","texHtml":"The table shows the number of people in different age groups at a cinema.\n<div class=\"pp-table-wrap\"><table class=\"pp-table\"><tr><th>Age (years)</th><th>Number of people</th></tr><tr><td>15 ≤ y < 25</td><td>35</td></tr><tr><td>25 ≤ y < 30</td><td>32</td></tr><tr><td>30 ≤ y < 50</td><td>44</td></tr><tr><td>50 ≤ y < 80</td><td>12</td></tr></table></div>\n\nDexter draws a histogram to show this information.\nThe height of the bar he draws for the group 15 ≤ y < 25 is 7 cm.\nCalculate the height of each of the remaining bars.\n\n25 ≤ y < 30  \\\\\n30 ≤ y < 50  \\\\\n50 ≤ y < 80"},{"id":"0580-2019MayJune-Paper22-Q19","paper":"2019MayJune-Paper22","qnum":19,"marks":4,"topics":["Algebra and graphs"],"s":"2.5","d":2,"cat":"algebra","topic":"Equations","qtype":"equations","g":"mixed","src":"0580/22/M/J/19 Q19","year":2019,"session":"MayJune","tex":"Rearrange this formula to make m the subject.\n\\[P = \\dfrac{k + m}{m}\\]","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"recall","cmd":"rearrange"},{"id":"0580-2019MayJune-Paper22-Q20","paper":"2019MayJune-Paper22","qnum":20,"marks":4,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.9","d":2,"cat":"number","topic":"Estimation","qtype":"estimation and rounding","g":"mixed","src":"0580/22/M/J/19 Q20","year":2019,"session":"MayJune","tex":"Solve the equation \\(3x^2 - 2x - 10 = 0\\).\nShow all your working and give your answers correct to 2 decimal places.\n\nx =  or x =","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"solve"},{"id":"0580-2019MayJune-Paper22-Q21","paper":"2019MayJune-Paper22","qnum":21,"marks":4,"topics":["Number","Geometry","Probability"],"s":"1.2","d":2,"cat":"number","topic":"Sets","qtype":"sets and Venn diagrams","g":"mixed","src":"0580/22/M/J/19 Q21","year":2019,"session":"MayJune","tex":"(a) In the Venn diagram, shade \\(X \\cap \\overline{Y}\\).\n\n(b) The Venn diagram below shows information about the number of gardeners who grow melons (M), potatoes (P) and carrots (C).\n\n(i) (c) A gardener is chosen at random from the gardeners who grow melons.\nFind the probability that this gardener does not grow carrots.\n\n(d) Find \\(n((M \\cap P) \\cup (C \\setminus (M \\cup P)))\\).","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":1},{"label":"(b)","marks":0},{"label":"(c)","marks":2},{"label":"(d)","marks":1}],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"draw"},{"id":"0580-2019MayJune-Paper22-Q22","paper":"2019MayJune-Paper22","qnum":22,"marks":4,"topics":["Transformations and vectors"],"s":"7.1","d":2,"cat":"vectors","topic":"Transformations","qtype":"transformations","g":"mixed","src":"0580/22/M/J/19 Q22","year":2019,"session":"MayJune","tex":"\\[A = \\begin{pmatrix} 2 & 7 \\\\ 1 & 3 \\end{pmatrix}, \\quad B = \\begin{pmatrix} 3 & 4 \\\\ 0 & 1 \\end{pmatrix}\\]\n\n(a) Calculate AB.\n\n(b) Find \\(A^{-1}\\), the inverse of A.","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":2},{"label":"(b)","marks":2}],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate"},{"id":"0580-2019MayJune-Paper22-Q23","paper":"2019MayJune-Paper22","qnum":23,"marks":4,"topics":["Coordinate geometry","Geometry","Transformations and vectors"],"s":"3.6","d":2,"cat":"coord","topic":"Parallel lines","qtype":"parallel lines","g":"mixed","src":"0580/22/M/J/19 Q23","year":2019,"session":"MayJune","tex":"ABCD is a parallelogram with \\(\\overrightarrow{AB} = \\mathbf{q}\\) and \\(\\overrightarrow{AD} = \\mathbf{p}\\).\nABM is a straight line with AB : BM = 1 : 1.\nADN is a straight line with AD : DN = 3 : 2.\n\n(a) Write \\(\\overrightarrow{MN}\\), in terms of \\(\\mathbf{p}\\) and \\(\\mathbf{q}\\), in its simplest form.\n\n\\(\\overrightarrow{MN} =\\) \n\n(b) The straight line NM cuts BC at X.\nX is the midpoint of MN.\n\\(\\overrightarrow{BX} = k\\mathbf{q}\\)\nFind the value of k.\n\nk =","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":2},{"label":"(b)","marks":2}],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"find"},{"id":"0580-2019MayJune-Paper22-Q24","paper":"2019MayJune-Paper22","qnum":24,"marks":4,"topics":["Geometry","Mensuration"],"s":"4.6","d":2,"cat":"geometry","topic":"Angles","qtype":"angle calculations","g":"mixed","src":"0580/22/M/J/19 Q24","year":2019,"session":"MayJune","tex":"ABCDEFGH is a cuboid.\nAB = 18 cm, BC = 7 cm and CG = 12 cm.\nCalculate the angle that the diagonal AG makes with the base ABCD.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate"},{"id":"0580-2019MayJune-Paper22-Q25","paper":"2019MayJune-Paper22","qnum":25,"marks":6,"topics":["Coordinate geometry","Geometry"],"s":"3.1","d":2,"cat":"coord","topic":"Coordinates","qtype":"coordinates reading/plotting","g":"graph","src":"0580/22/M/J/19 Q25","year":2019,"session":"MayJune","tex":"[Question 25 content to be completed - coordinate geometry question with points A, B, C]","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"recall","cmd":"other"}]